      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## Q6 - One-Hot to 4-Bit Binary Encoding Layer\n",
        "\n",
        "A network classifies digits 0-9 with a 10-neuron one-hot output. Design a final **4-neuron layer** that converts this into a **4-bit binary** encoding (e.g. digit 5 outputs 0101). Specify the weight matrix and bias vector.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Design and Reasoning:**\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Your answer:**\n",
        "Since the input is a clean one-hot vector, only index column $j$ is active ($1$) for digit $j$. We can explicitly design our matrix $W$ such that column $j$ contains the 4-bit binary representation of integer $j$. By mapping $1$s to weights of $1.0$ and $0$s to weights of $0.0$, the matrix multiplication $W \\cdot \\text{one\\_hot}$ acts as a lookup table that extracts the exact binary representation. No bias compensation is needed, so we set $b = 0$ everywhere."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "c537923e",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c537923e"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Construct the 4x10 matrix dynamically by extracting bits for each digit\n",
        "W = np.zeros((4, 10))\n",
        for digit in range(10):\n",
        "    # Convert digit to 4-bit binary string array: e.g., 5 -> [0, 1, 0, 1]\n",
        "    binary_string = format(digit, '04b')\n",
        "    W[:, digit] = [float(char) for char in binary_string]\n",
        "\n",
        "b_enc = np.zeros(4)\n",
        "\n",
        "def threshold(x):\n",
        "    return (x >= 0.5).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Digit | Output | Expected | OK?')\n",
        "print('-' * 35)\n",
        "for digit in range(10):\n",
        "    one_hot = np.zeros(10)\n",
        "    one_hot[digit] = 1.0\n",
        "    out = threshold(W @ one_hot + b_enc)\n",
        "    expected = format(digit, '04b')\n",
        "    ok = 'OK' if ''.join(map(str, out)) == expected else 'FAIL'\n",
        "    print(f'  {digit}   |  {out}  |  {expected}  | {ok}')"
      ]
    },
    {
