      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "## Q7 - Geometric Interpretation of 1D Gradient Descent\n",
        "\n",
        "Consider C(v) as a function of a single scalar v.\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Give a precise **geometric interpretation** of the update rule v = v - alpha * dC/dv.\n",
        "2. How do the slope and the learning rate alpha physically dictate movement along the curve?\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Your answer:**\n",
        "1. Geometrically, the term $\\frac{dC}{dv}$ represents the slope of the tangent line touching the function at position $v$. Subtracting this value moves $v$ in the opposite direction of the slope, effectively rolling down the curve toward its local minimum.\n",
        "2. The step size is determined by multiplying the learning rate $\\alpha$ by the slope magnitude. When the curve is steep, the gradient is large, resulting in larger steps. As the parameters approach a flat basin or minimum, the slope shrinks toward zero, naturally slowing down the update steps for fine-grained convergence."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "7dcfa248",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7dcfa248"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "v_vals = np.linspace(-3, 5, 300)\n",
        "C_v = (v_vals - 2)**2 + 1\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
        "plt.plot(v_vals, C_v, label='C(v)', color='purple')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Run GD steps and annotate\n",
        "v_init = -2.0\n",
        "alpha = 0.25\n",
        "curr_v = v_init\n",
        "\n",
        "for step in range(4):\n",
        "    cost_curr = (curr_v - 2)**2 + 1\n",
        "    grad_curr = 2 * (curr_v - 2)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Annotate on graph\n",
        "    plt.plot(curr_v, cost_curr, 'go')\n",
        "    plt.annotate(f'Step {step}', xy=(curr_v, cost_curr), xytext=(curr_v + 0.2, cost_curr + 1.5),\n",
        "                 arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', shrink=0.05, width=1, headwidth=4))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    curr_v = curr_v - alpha * grad_curr\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.xlabel('v')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('C(v)')\n",
        "plt.title('1D Gradient Descent Iteration Walkdown')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
