        "---\n",
        "## Q8 - Zero Hidden Layers: What Model Are You Really Training?\n",
        "\n",
        "Suppose you remove all hidden layers, connecting 784 inputs directly to 10 outputs, trained with SGD.\n",
        "\n",
        "1. What **mathematical model** have you effectively created?\n",
        "2. Why is classification accuracy **fundamentally capped**?\n",
        "3. What does this imply about the **necessity of hidden layers**?\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Your answer:**\n",
        "1. You have built a basic **Linear Classifier** (equivalent to Multinomial Logistic Regression or a set of parallel single-layer Perceptrons).\n",
        "2. Accuracy is capped because linear models can only construct straight decision boundaries (hyperplanes). They cannot handle datasets that are not linearly separable (such as an XOR configuration or complex image patterns like handwritten digits in MNIST).\n",
        "3. This underscores that hidden layers are essential for intermediate feature extraction. They apply non-linear transformations that warp the input space, projecting entangled data into a space where classes become cleanly, linearly separable."
      ]
